  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Carpenter",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Survey work sites and verify measurements against construction drawings to ensure accuracy and compliance</li><li>Procure and requisition necessary materials to support timely construction work</li><li>Prepare and cut materials to specified sizes for furniture assembly, ensuring precision and quality</li><li>Lead and supervise junior carpenters in assembling furniture and performing finishing tasks to meet quality standards</li><li>Direct junior carpenters in installing customized furniture on-site, ensuring proper fit and finish</li><li>Enforce safety protocols and implement precautionary measures to maintain a safe work environment</li><li>Manage project timelines by delegating tasks effectively to junior carpenters and monitoring progress</li><li>Inspect workmanship regularly and address customer complaints promptly to uphold service excellence</li><li>Conduct periodic maintenance and checks on all machines, equipment, and tools to ensure operational readiness</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Completion of GCE 'O' Level or higher</li><li>Minimum of 5 years’ experience in comprehensive carpentry construction work</li><li>Ability to read and interpret construction drawings accurately</li><li>Proficient in operating carpentry machines and equipment</li><li>Demonstrated leadership skills in managing a team of junior carpenters</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills with attention to detail</li><li>Effective communication skills to liaise with customers professionally</li><li>Possession of a Class 3 Driving License is advantageous</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
